                        </msIdentifier>
                        <msContents>
                            <summary>
                                <p>The text appears to be an early form of missal which includes the Station churches in Rome in the rubrics (beginning and ending with St Maria Maggiore, <locus from="12v" to="12v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="233v" to="233v" scheme="folios"/>). The text on <locus from="11r" to="284v" scheme="folios"/> agrees to large extent to the content and order of the text in the Gregorian Sacramentary Cambrai Bibliothéque Municipale MS 164 from the early 9th century, but with added Bible readings and antiphons, cf. <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107561">Deshusses (1971)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="99" to="295" unit="page"/>
                                        <citedRange from="303" to="334" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>. The Proper of Time is followed by a Proper of Saints, which ends in November, after which a set of prayers for Advent introduces a collection of prayers, blessings and related texts. The final text in the manusript is a Proper of Time from Pentecost on without mention of Station churches and with formularies only for Sundays, Wednesdays, and sometimes Fridays.</p>
                            </summary>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        The calendar is not complete. It begins with the Seven Virgins (9 Apr.) and ends with St Sylvester (31 Dec.).</p>
                                    <p>
                                        For a complete transcription and discussion, see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107560">Tüchle (1978)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="202" to="208" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1rb" to="1rb" scheme="folios"/>: Sts Gordianus and Epimachus (10 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1vb" to="1vb" scheme="folios"/>: St Ulric (4 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2rb" to="2rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Afra (7 Aug.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2va" to="2va" scheme="folios"/>: St Magnus (6 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3ra" to="3ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Gallus (15, 16 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3ra" to="3ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Columbanus (24 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3ra" to="3ra" scheme="folios"/>: St Pirminus (3 Nov);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3rb" to="3rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Fridolin (15 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3rb" to="3rb" scheme="folios"/>: St Otmar (16 Nov.).</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="4r" to="4r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Prayers for St Mark </title>
                                <incipit>
                                    <supplied reason="omitted">D</supplied>EUS QUI BEATVM MARCVM EVANGELISTAM TVVM EVANGElice predicationis gratia sublimasti </incipit>
                                <explicit>atque pontifice tuo marco plena uirtute consequamur P</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="4v" to="10r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Ordo and Canon missae</title>
                                <rubric>
                                    <del>IN NOMINE DOMINI INC</del> IN NOMINE DOMINI INCPIT LIBER SACRAMENTORVM DE CIRCULO ANNI EXPOSITVS A SANCTO GREGORIO PAPA ROMANO EDITVS EX AUTHENTICO LIBRO BIBLIOTHECAE CV<supplied reason="illegible">BICU</supplied>LI SCRIPTUS QVALITER MISSA ROMANA CELEBRATVR </rubric>
                                <incipit>HOC EST INPRIMIS INTROITVS</incipit>
                                <explicit>AGNUS DEI QUI TOLLIS PECCATA MUNDI MISERERE NOBIS</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="7r" to="7r" scheme="folios"/>: Canon.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="10r" to="10v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Prayers for the Virgin Mary</title>
                                <rubric>IN ADNVNTIATIONE SANCTAE MARIAE</rubric>
                                <incipit>OMNIPOTENS SEMPER BEATUS QVI COETERNUM TIBI FILII HODIE PRO mundi salute</incipit>
                                <explicit>christi filii tui incarnationem cognouimus per passionem eius et crucem ad resurretionis gloriam perducamur Per</explicit>
                                <note>After the final line a second contemporary hand has added 8 lines: <quote>Hodierne lux diei celebris in matris dei agitur memoria <gap reason="editorial"/> florentis hortus haustro stante porta clausa post et ante</quote>.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="11r" to="242v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of Time</title>
                                <rubric>IN VIGILIA NATALIS DOMINI DE DONA </rubric>
                                <incipit>HODIE SCIEtis quia ueniet dominus </incipit>
                                <explicit>Sic est qui sibi thesaurizat et non est in deum diues (Luke 12:21)</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>Leaves in wrong order; the correct order is: <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="149" to="149" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="151" to="151" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="150" to="150" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <locus from="152" to="152" scheme="folios"/>
                                        </locusGrp>.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>The Proper of Time begins with Christmas Eve and ends with Wednesday in the Octave of Pentecost.</p>
                                    <p>The easter mass on <locus from="150v" to="184r" scheme="folios"/> includes the Trisagion in Greek and Latin (<locus from="159v" to="159v" scheme="folios"/>), and instructions for baptism/catechumen. There is also a longer litany on <locus from="179v" to="181v" scheme="folios"/>, which inlcludes Sts Gordianus and Epimachus, St Ulric, and St Afra.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="242v" to="284v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of Saints</title>
                                <rubric>mense iunio kalende iunii Dedicatio sancti nicomedis </rubric>
                                <incipit>ANTIPHONA LAETABITUR IUSTUS DOMINUS QUI NOS BEATI nicomedis martyris tui meritis </incipit>
                                <explicit>ut tuo semper auxilio secuta tibi possit deuotione seruire Per</explicit>
                                <note>Begins with the Dedication of St Nicomedes (1 June) and ends with (<locus from="283v" to="283v" scheme="folios"/>) St Andrew (30 Nov.).</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="284v" to="296r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Prayer collection</title>
                                <rubric>MENSE DECEMBRIO ORATIONES DE ADUENTU DOMINI</rubric>
                                <explicit>eorum pariter cottidie auxiliis ab omnibus protegamur aduersis Per dominum</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="285v" to="285v" scheme="folios"/>: various prayers;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="285v" to="287v" scheme="folios"/>: pro peccatis;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="287v" to="290v" scheme="folios"/>; orationes cotidiani;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="290v" to="292v" scheme="folios"/>: orationes matutinales, vespertinales;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="292v" to="293r" scheme="folios"/>: orationes cotidianis diebus ad missas;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="293r" to="296r" scheme="folios"/>: common of saints.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="296r" to="301r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="uniform">Mass formulary for the entire week</title>
                                <rubric>DIE DOMINICA DE SANCTA TRINITATE</rubric>
                                <incipit>BENEDICTA SIT SANCTA TRINITAS atque indiuisa unitas confitebimur</incipit>
                                <explicit>da quesumus eius nos patrocinus ubique protegi in cuius ueneratione hec tuae obtulimus maiestati Per</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="296r" to="296r" scheme="folios"/>: dominica: de trinitate;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="297r" to="297r" scheme="folios"/>: feria II, Pro peccatis;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="298r" to="298r" scheme="folios"/>: feria III, Ad postulanda angelica suffragia;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="298v" to="298v" scheme="folios"/>: feria IIII, De sapientia;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="299r" to="299r" scheme="folios"/>: feria V, De caritate;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="300r" to="300r" scheme="folios"/>: feria VI, De sancta cruce;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="300v" to="300v" scheme="folios"/>: Sabbato, De sancta Maria.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="301r" to="333v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Collection of prayers and masses</title>
                                <rubric>DE SPIRITUS SANCTI DONO POSTULANDO </rubric>
                                <incipit>Antiphona Dum sanctificatus fuero in uobis </incipit>
                                <explicit>ALLELUIA Diffusa est gratia in labiis tuis propterea benedixit te deus in eternum</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="301r" to="301r" scheme="folios"/>: de spiritus sancti dono postulando;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="301v" to="307v" scheme="folios"/>: various masses;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="308r" to="311v" scheme="folios"/>: missae communis;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="311v" to="317v" scheme="folios"/>: various masses, masses for the sick;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="318v" to="328v" scheme="folios"/>: masses for the dead;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="328v" to="333v" scheme="folios"/>: various prayers, starting with orationes ante cibum;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="331r" to="332v" scheme="folios"/>: prefaces;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="332v" to="333r" scheme="folios"/>: blessings;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="333r" to="333v" scheme="folios"/>: halleluia.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="334r" to="372v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of Time (continued)</title>
                                <rubric>DOMINICA I POST PENTECOSTEN</rubric>
                                <incipit>DOMINE IN TUA MISERICORDIA speraui exultauit cor meum</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">At illi cogitabant intra se dicentes quia si dixerimus de (Luke 20:5)</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>Begins with the First Sunday after Pentecost and ends (defectively) on Friday in the Fifteenth Week after Pentecost.</p>
                                    <p>No saints mentioned. Consists of formularies for Sundays and Wednesdays, sometimes Fridays.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
